        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 2:14PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Basin, or near Boulder, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boulder, Basin, Wickes, and Elkhorn State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
